summary: This document is an email chain from May 2020 discussing the status of FBI 302 interview reports and handwritten notes related to the Epstein case. The correspondents are coordinating to identify missing documents and clarify which interviews have associated notes versus just formal 302 reports, referencing over 120 interviews conducted.

events.title: Interview on July 6, 2019
events.description: An interview was conducted, for which a copy of the interviewee's ID was provided but no written notes were found, only a very short 302 report.

keyFacts: The correspondence indicates there were more than 120 interviews conducted in the Epstein case investigation.
The email chain is focused on reconciling FBI 302 reports with handwritten interview notes, identifying missing documents.
Specific interviews are referenced as missing either their 302 report or accompanying notes, suggesting a large volume of investigative material.
The document shows administrative follow-up between parties involved in managing the case documents, highlighting the scale of the investigation.
